records.addlTxt: Amended
Count 1 & 2
Report from Pre-Trial Supervision Program dated July 14, 2016

Defendant James S Cattanach in court with attorney Acalia N Halverson. Cass W Cousins appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

9:52 a.m.  Court calls case and states the appearances.
Amended Information filed by the State.

Plea questionnaire/Agreement filed.
Prosecutor states plea agreement.
Attorney for Defendant concurs with agreement stated.

Defendant enters a plea of: 
Count 1 - No contest 
Count 2 - No contest 

Court questions Defendant regarding plea.
Court informs Defendant of Constitutional Rights. Court advises Defendant of Elements State must prove for the Charge.
Court questions Attorney for Defendant.
Court finds Defendant's Plea is freely, voluntarily and intelligently made.
Attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charge(s).
State has complied with victim notification - one victim appears in Court today and does not intend to make a statement in Court.

BY THE COURT:
Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charge(s).
Court finds the defendant guilty on Count 1 & 2.  Clerk directed to enter Judgment of Conviction this date.

Atty Cousins makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Atty Halverson makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Defendant makes a statement prior to sentencing.

BY THE COURT:
Count 1 -
Impose/Stay 180 day jail sentence
First half in jail with huber priveleges for work, counseling and any other reason the sheriff will allow
Second half on GPS electric home monitoring if approved by jail administration and risk assessment 
Placed on Probation for 18 months:
Early discharge from probation if recommended and approved by the Agent 
**Conditions of Probation are:
Pay restitution in the amount of $1,500; minimum payment of $150/month
Write a letter of apology to the officer's within 30 days and provide to agent for approval
Participate in any counseling and assessments as recommended by the agent.
Pay costs
Pay Surcharges - DNA 
Provide DNA sample
Zero jail credit

Count 2 -
Impose/Stay 60 day jail sentence - concurrent to count 1
First half in jail with huber priveleges for work, counseling and any other reason the sheriff will allow
Second half on GPS electric home monitoring if approved by jail administration and risk assessment 
Placed on Probation for 18 months concurrent to Count 1:
Early discharge for probation if recommended and approved by the Agent 
**Conditions of Probation are:
Comply with conditions in Count 1 
Pay costs
Pay surcharges - DNA

20 days to appeal
Report filed by Pre-Trial Supervision Program, Case Manager
